Big Brother Naija 2017 contestant Uriel Oputa and comedian/actor Emma Oh My God will host dating show, Hello, Mr. Right Nigeria, on St Novela E at 8:30pm from November 1. According to StarTimes, the organisers of the show, Hello Mr. Right Naija, will integrate dating and entertainment in redefining matchmaking for contestants while entertaining the audience at home. The Public Relations Manager at StarTimes, Kunmi Balogun, said: “Hello Mr. Right is exclusive to StarTimes and the first of its kind in Nigeria. The show will see contestants partake in an impartial and open dating platform where they make a pitch to be selected by fellow contestants. The lucky pairs who emerge winners will walk away with prizes worth N2million.” Uriel and Emma Oh My God were selected to host the show after being considered as a perfect fit to drive home the quality of entertainment the show brings to the audience.